article.headline: Arizona 78, Washington State 51
article.story:
TUCSON, Ariz.(AP) -- Arizona's full-court trapping press rattled
Washington State as Shawtinice Polk's double-double sparked the
Wildcats to a 78-51 victory on Monday night.

Polk scored 19 points and had 17 boards for her second straight
double-double. She had 19 points and 15 rebounds on Saturday in a
victory over Washington.

Arizona won its ninth straight game overall and recorded its
20th consecutive home victory, the sixth longest streak nationally.

Polk reached double figures in each category by halftime with 10
points and 11 rebounds, but her inside game added to a full-court
trap defense that put Washington State away midway through the
second half.

Washington State (4-7, 0-2) closed a 13-point lead to 41-35 on
Candace Fields' three-point play with 13:38 remaining in the game.
Polk countered with an offensive put-back, which started a 14-0
run.

When Arizona (10-2, 2-0) was not getting the ball inside to
Polk, the Wildcats were converting steals and Cougar turnovers into
layups with a tenacious press.

Dee-Dee Wheeler, who scored 19 points, added six points in the
crucial span including a layup off a Polk assist for a 55-35 lead
with nearly nine minutes remaining.

Washington State's 5 minute, nine second scoring drought ended
on a Jessica Perry lay-in with 8:31 left.

Natalie Jones added 13 points for Arizona. Washington State was
led by the 12 points from Perry, while Kim Dugan had 10.
